// One infinite loop followed by another: L1 (just node 1, self-looping with a break to L2)
// then L2 (just node 2, self-looping forever with no exit). L1 alone has an outgoing edge to
// node 2, so its SCC isn't terminal — it can escape to L2. L2 is the only terminal SCC.
// One impossible edge return_ -> 2 makes post-domination total: pd(0)=1, pd(1)=2, pd(2)=return_.
//
//        0
//        |
//     ->1
//    |  | \____
//     --       |
//             ->2
//              \_|

code,0,1
cond,1,1,2
code,2,2
